# Network Troubleshooting Tools

## Commands

```bash
hostname
hostnamectl
ping
traceroute
tracepath
nslookup
dig
```

---

## Purpose

### ping

Tests connectivity.

### traceroute

Shows packet path.

### tracepath

Alternative to traceroute.

### nslookup

Checks DNS resolution.

### dig

Provides detailed DNS information.

---

## Troubleshooting Order

1. Verify connectivity using ping.
2. Check routing using traceroute or tracepath.
3. Verify DNS using nslookup or dig.
